From: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 9 Jun 2026 14:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] amplifiers: cs40l26: set cs40l26_loaded before MFD child probe
 fires

cs40l26_probe() calls devm_mfd_add_devices() which immediately
instantiates the cs40l26-codec child platform device, whose probe
runs synchronously and short-circuits with:

    if (!cs40l26_loaded) {
        dev_err(... "Skipping cs40l26-codec probe");
        return -EIO;
    }

But cs40l26_loaded is only set TRUE on the very next line in
cs40l26_probe(), after MFD has already run the child probe. So
the codec child never binds, the snd_soc component is never
registered, and monaco-asoc-snd's Secondary MI2S dai_link to
"cs40l26_codec" never resolves -- no audio path to the speaker
even though the parent (haptic) side is fine.

Set cs40l26_loaded = true BEFORE devm_mfd_add_devices() so the
codec child sees the right state. If MFD fails, the err path
calls cs40l26_remove() which already clears the flag.

This is a Pixel Watch 2 (pixel-watch branch) driver-internal race;
the dr-eos branch's codec probe doesn't have the !cs40l26_loaded
check at all.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [aurora-specific HW glue; upstream
                                should reorder this if they kept
                                the !cs40l26_loaded check]

Signed-off-by: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>
---
 private/google-modules/amplifiers/cs40l26/cs40l26.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/private/google-modules/amplifiers/cs40l26/cs40l26.c b/private/google-modules/amplifiers/cs40l26/cs40l26.c
--- a/private/google-modules/amplifiers/cs40l26/cs40l26.c
+++ b/private/google-modules/amplifiers/cs40l26/cs40l26.c
@@ -4950,6 +4950,8 @@ int cs40l26_probe(struct cs40l26_private *cs40l26,

 	INIT_LIST_HEAD(&cs40l26->effect_head);

+	cs40l26_loaded = true;
+
 	ret = devm_mfd_add_devices(dev, PLATFORM_DEVID_AUTO, cs40l26_devs,
 			CS40L26_NUM_MFD_DEVS, NULL, 0, NULL);
 	if (ret) {
@@ -4957,7 +4959,6 @@ int cs40l26_probe(struct cs40l26_private *cs40l26,
 		goto err;
 	}

-	cs40l26_loaded = true;
 	return 0;
 err:
 	cs40l26_remove(cs40l26);
